  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advancing Higher Education For Afghanistan&#x2019;s Development  (AHEAD)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Afghanistan):  Advancing Higher Education for Afghanistan&apos;s Development (AHEAD) is a planned higher education activity to produce a cadre of educated and professionally-qualified Afghan women and men, leading to a more informed and engaged civil society. AHEAD will work with the Ministry of Higher Education, Afghan public and private universities to: 1) Increase access to Higher Education (HE) opportunities, especially for women; 2) Improve the quality and relevance of HE programs aligned with market needs; and 3) Enhance the management capacity of both the Ministry of Higher Education (MoHE) and universities. Achieving these objectives will lead to greater citizen participation in local and national issues of importance to Afghanistan, and will foster appreciation for diversity and promote a culture of tolerance and peaceful co-existence as well as civic pride. USAID assistance will include forging regional and international public-private partnerships between universities, improving the quality of instruction and research, expanding the use of technology and other tools to deliver cutting edge instruction, and developing networks and associations that help solve tasks and promote democratic values in the process. Promotion of technology will enable Afghan Higher Education Institutions to consider varieties of teaching approaches including online learning that will reduce the impact COVID-19 and similar viral infections, which limit physical attendance at the universities. ..Using FY 2020 funds, USAID will provide students with updated curricula and learning experiences aligned with market needs and industry best practice, and will strengthen higher education management systems necessary to sustain education quality for a better educated cadre of professional Afghans. This activity contributes to the Integrated Country Strategy Goal-4 to promote inclusive growth by improving civic education and democratic culture, as well as higher education quality and management</narrative>
  </description>
